<Content>Faded elegance and too overpriced I was quite excited to stay at the Langham - Hotwire rates the hotel as 4.5 stars and I got a great price. However, after my stay I can say I was unimpressed. Here are my comments:The rooms were nice but nothing spectacular. I did like that a bathrobe was provided, and even slippers! However, there wasn't a pen but rather a pencil. Who writes postcards or letters using a pencil? Staff did come in to the room in the evening to provide chocolates and the next day's weather.Room service was way overpriced. $25 for breakfast before delivery fees, service charges, etc. My calculation was it would really be close to $36 by the time all the additional charges were added on.The cocktail lounge was old world elegance and there was a piano player, but $14 for a martini? Come on!One the biggest disappointments for me was the afternoon tea. I had never attended one before so thought this would be the perfect opportunity to do so. I emailed the hotel and received a reply that I should book well in advance. When I showed up, there were only 2 other people there and it didn't change the whole time I was there. In addition, it must have been between lunch and dinner because staff was changing the chairs at the tables around mine, making a lot of banging noises for what I think should have been a peaceful, quite experience.The newspaper provided was a financial newspaper from London, I think. Why not a local paper?Internet service is $10 for 24-hours. Not bad, although I didn't use it.Then, after confirming the charges to my room and receiving my final bill, I checked my credit card account online a few days later to find an additional charge for $4.55. I contacted my credit card company to dispute the charge and they have removed it for now. What could I possibly have purchased or used that would only cost $4.55 at a hotel that charges $25 for breakfast? I bet I couldn't even get coffee for that!All in all, I felt this was a hotel trying too hard to rely on its faded, old world elegance. That, combined with its location, make it not a place I will look to stay at unless I can continue to get a great deal. 
