<Author>theroadlesstravelled
<Content>Beautiful Building, too many glitches I booked a room through the property directly as it was a last minute trip and I did not want any surprises. The reservation person (manger in charge), was unable to verify that I had a room the next day, (given the short notice), and assured me that she would call me the following morning, (hopefully before I left for Boston). This happens all the time. She did not call, but I did, and after much confusion and waiting, another person was pretty sure that we had a room. I charged the $340 and hoped for the best.The hotel was a little hard to find, but we got there okay after a long day. IT REALLY IS IN A GREAT LOCATION. The good news is that we not only had a room, but it was on the top floor. The staff were polite and the wait was not long. Getting off the elevator, we were assaulted by cigar smoke. It was thick and pervasive. It seemed to follow us to our room.Our room was nice and clean and fairly spacious with a row of slanted windows,-but it was shockingly hot. I tried to call the main desk for 15 minutes and it was busy. We had enough time to change and run to our dinner reservation, but notified them of the problem on the way out.When we returned, we learned that engineering was unable to fix the problem. They did have a room for us on the 2nd floor-so we took it. DId I mention that one of the three elevators was out of order? That we packed up in the heat with an exhausted child? There was no offer of help and the process was quite frustrating and long. They did offer to comp the breakfast, but we had already paid for it.The new room was spacious-(24X30?), 12 foot ceilings-and looked out onto a little park. (Luckily they had good black out blinds.) There were 2 huge windows but it was quiet. The bathroom was nice-very clean with marble everything. Decent size. Good water pressure, many towels. King sized bed was confortable, (nice soft linens, hard pillows), and there was a good seating area. They had not cleared out the mini refrigerator as requested and it was late so I didn't bother to call. After 10 PM, they called, waking me and my son up, to ask if we wanted them to come and do it then. I did not. I ended up throwing away food as a result.The noise level at the hotel was great-hardly heard anyone else. The pool was nice-small but with lanes. Plenty of natural light, clean. Some floatation devices for the kids. Adequate hot tub. The exercise room consisted of free weights and 6 cardio machines. While in the exercise room, you can watch your family below in the pool through a glass wall. The bathrooms had changing areas. There were 2 employees on duty so it was safe and professional.The breakfast area was pretty but the service was HORRIBLE. Our waiter was arguing with his assistant and they managed to disapppear from our entire corner of the restaurant. (My fellow patrons and I tried in vain to locate them.) The food was avearage but overpriced, ($25 each), and our orders were wrong. There was indifference from the wait staff so we did not press the issue. The irony is that we ended up OVER tipping because we could not wait longer than 19 minutes for them to collect the check. Go elsewhere!We paid for late check out-but found housekeeping cleaning amongst our belongings with the door wide open when we returned to our room. I had wanted to give my son a bath, but she insisted that we wait as she was, almost done. I do not fault her, but obviously the communication was poor as she did not believe we were supossed to be there.Sigh. The really good news: they took 50% off the bill when I went downstairs to complain that the maid would not leave. I would have rated this property higher if there had not been so many glitches. 
